  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Instrument+Serif:ital@0;1&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  <style>
    *,*::before,*::after{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}html{scroll-behavior:smooth}
    body{background:#050D05;color:#F0FFF0;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;font-weight:300;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased}
    nav{position:fixed;top:0;left:0;right:0;z-index:50;background:rgba(5,13,5,0.95);backdrop-filter:blur(12px);border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A}
    .nav-inner{max-width:1200px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 2.5rem;height:64px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between}
    .nav-logo{font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif;font-size:1.3rem;font-style:italic;color:#F0FFF0;text-decoration:none}
    .nav-link{font-size:0.82rem;color:rgba(240,255,240,0.5);text-decoration:none}.nav-link:hover{color:#F0FFF0}
    .btn-p{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;background:#00C853;color:#050D05;padding:0.875rem 1.75rem;font-size:0.85rem;font-weight:600;text-decoration:none;border:none;cursor:pointer;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif}.btn-p:hover{opacity:0.88}
    .btn-g{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;background:transparent;color:#F0FFF0;padding:0.875rem 1.75rem;font-size:0.85rem;font-weight:600;text-decoration:none;border:1px solid #1A3A1A;cursor:pointer;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif}
    .badge{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;font-size:0.72rem;font-weight:500;color:#00C853;letter-spacing:0.06em;margin-bottom:1.5rem}
    .badge-dot{width:7px;height:7px;border-radius:50%;background:#00C853;animation:pulse 2s infinite}
    @keyframes pulse{0%,100%{opacity:1}50%{opacity:0.4}}
    .lbl{font-size:0.68rem;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#00C853;margin-bottom:0.75rem;display:block}
    section{padding:5rem 2.5rem;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A}.sec-inner{max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto}
    .hero{min-height:45vh;display:flex;align-items:center;padding:7rem 2.5rem 4rem}.hero-inner{max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto;width:100%}
    .hero-h{font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif;font-size:clamp(2.5rem,5vw,3.75rem);font-weight:400;line-height:1.1;color:#F0FFF0;margin-bottom:1.25rem}
    .hero-sub{font-size:1rem;color:#C0D8C0;line-height:1.75;max-width:720px}
    .byline{font-size:0.82rem;color:#8FAF8F;margin-top:1.5rem}
    .byline a{color:#00C853;text-decoration:none}
    .h2{font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif;font-size:clamp(1.8rem,3.5vw,2.4rem);font-weight:400;line-height:1.15;color:#F0FFF0;margin-bottom:1.25rem}
    .body{font-size:0.98rem;color:#C0D8C0;line-height:1.85;max-width:760px;margin-bottom:1rem}.body em{color:#F0FFF0;font-style:italic}

    .calc-inputs{background:#0A1A0A;border:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:2rem;margin-bottom:2rem}
    .question{padding:1.5rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A}
    .question:last-child{border-bottom:none}
    .question .qnum{font-size:0.68rem;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#00C853;margin-bottom:0.4rem;display:block}
    .question .qtext{font-size:1rem;color:#F0FFF0;line-height:1.55;margin-bottom:1rem;font-weight:400}
    .answer-row{display:flex;gap:0.75rem}
    .ans-btn{flex:0 0 auto;background:transparent;color:#C0D8C0;padding:0.6rem 1.5rem;font-size:0.85rem;font-weight:500;border:1px solid #1A3A1A;cursor:pointer;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;transition:all 0.15s}
    .ans-btn:hover{border-color:#00C853;color:#F0FFF0}
    .ans-btn.selected{background:rgba(0,200,83,0.12);border-color:#00C853;color:#00C853}
    .progress{display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;margin-top:1.5rem;padding-top:1.5rem;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A}
    .progress-text{font-size:0.82rem;color:#8FAF8F}
    .progress-bar{flex:1;height:4px;background:#1A3A1A;margin:0 1rem;position:relative}
    .progress-fill{position:absolute;top:0;left:0;height:100%;background:#00C853;transition:width 0.25s}

    .result-card{background:#0A1A0A;border:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:2.5rem;margin-top:2rem;display:none}
    .result-card.shown{display:block}
    .tier-tag{display:inline-block;padding:0.4rem 0.9rem;font-size:0.72rem;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:1.25rem}
    .tier-tag.t1{background:rgba(255,82,82,0.12);color:#FF5252;border:1px solid rgba(255,82,82,0.4)}
    .tier-tag.t2{background:rgba(255,152,0,0.12);color:#FF9800;border:1px solid rgba(255,152,0,0.4)}
    .tier-tag.t3{background:rgba(255,193,7,0.12);color:#FFC107;border:1px solid rgba(255,193,7,0.4)}
    .tier-tag.t4{background:rgba(0,200,83,0.12);color:#00C853;border:1px solid rgba(0,200,83,0.4)}
    .tier-head{font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif;font-size:clamp(1.8rem,3vw,2.4rem);font-weight:400;color:#F0FFF0;margin-bottom:0.4rem;line-height:1.15}
    .tier-score{font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif;font-style:italic;font-size:1.1rem;color:#8FAF8F;margin-bottom:1.5rem}
    .tier-verdict{font-size:1rem;color:#C0D8C0;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:2rem;max-width:780px}
    .rec-head{font-size:0.78rem;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#00C853;margin-bottom:1rem;display:block}
    .rec-list{list-style:none;padding:0}
    .rec-list li{padding:1rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;color:#F0FFF0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.65;display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:flex-start}
    .rec-list li:last-child{border-bottom:none}
    .rec-num{font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif;font-style:italic;font-size:1.3rem;color:#00C853;flex:0 0 auto;line-height:1.2}
    .rec-actions{display:flex;gap:0.75rem;margin-top:1.75rem;flex-wrap:wrap}

    .verdict{background:rgba(0,200,83,0.06);border-left:3px solid #00C853;padding:1.5rem 1.75rem;margin-top:2rem;max-width:780px}
    .verdict h3{font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif;color:#F0FFF0;font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:400;margin-bottom:0.5rem}
    .verdict p{color:#C0D8C0;font-size:0.92rem;line-height:1.7;margin:0}

    .faq-item{padding:1.5rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A}
    .faq-item:last-child{border-bottom:none}
    .faq-q{font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif;font-size:1.25rem;color:#F0FFF0;margin-bottom:0.6rem;font-weight:400}
    .faq-a{font-size:0.95rem;color:#C0D8C0;line-height:1.75;max-width:780px}

    .cta-box{background:#0A1A0A;border:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:3rem;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:2rem;flex-wrap:wrap}
    .cta-text{font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif;font-size:1.5rem;color:#F0FFF0}.cta-sub{font-size:0.88rem;color:#8FAF8F;margin-top:0.5rem}

    @media(max-width:900px){section{padding:3.5rem 1.5rem}.hide-mob{display:none!important}.cta-box{padding:2rem}.calc-inputs{padding:1.5rem}.result-card{padding:1.75rem}}
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<nav>
  <div class="nav-inner">
    <a href="/" class="nav-logo">Treetop</a>
    <div class="hide-mob" style="display:flex;gap:2rem;align-items:center;">
      <a href="/services" class="nav-link">Services</a>
      <a href="/pricing" class="nav-link">Pricing</a>
      <a href="/resources" class="nav-link">Resources</a>
      <a href="/about" class="nav-link">About</a>
    </div>
    <a href="/quiz" class="btn-p" style="padding:0.6rem 1.25rem;font-size:0.78rem;">Take the Gap Assessment &rarr;</a>
  </div>
</nav>

<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span>Free self-diagnostic &middot; 60 seconds &middot; 8 questions</div>
    <h1 class="hero-h">AI maturity tier <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">calculator.</em></h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">
      Answer 8 yes or no questions about how your team actually behaves around AI. Get your tier (Exploring, Piloting, Operationalizing, or Compounding), a short verdict on what that means, and three specific next steps you can take this quarter.
    </p>
    <p class="byline">By <a href="/about">Bill Colbert</a>, Founder, Treetop Growth Strategy.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <div class="calc-inputs">
      <span class="lbl">Answer all 8 to see your tier</span>

      <div class="question" data-q="1">
        <span class="qnum">Question 1 of 8</span>
        <p class="qtext">Does your CEO personally use AI tools (Claude, ChatGPT, or similar) on a daily basis?</p>
        <div class="answer-row">
          <button class="ans-btn" data-answer="yes" data-q="1">Yes</button>
          <button class="ans-btn" data-answer="no" data-q="1">No</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="question" data-q="2">
        <span class="qnum">Question 2 of 8</span>
        <p class="qtext">Do you have a named AI lead with 8 or more protected hours per week for workflow design?</p>
        <div class="answer-row">
          <button class="ans-btn" data-answer="yes" data-q="2">Yes</button>
          <button class="ans-btn" data-answer="no" data-q="2">No</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="question" data-q="3">
        <span class="qnum">Question 3 of 8</span>
        <p class="qtext">Are at least three major workflows (across any function) running on AI in production today?</p>
        <div class="answer-row">
          <button class="ans-btn" data-answer="yes" data-q="3">Yes</button>
          <button class="ans-btn" data-answer="no" data-q="3">No</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="question" data-q="4">
        <span class="qnum">Question 4 of 8</span>
        <p class="qtext">Are your AI workflows documented, indexed, and used by people other than the original author?</p>
        <div class="answer-row">
          <button class="ans-btn" data-answer="yes" data-q="4">Yes</button>
          <button class="ans-btn" data-answer="no" data-q="4">No</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="question" data-q="5">
        <span class="qnum">Question 5 of 8</span>
        <p class="qtext">Do new hires get trained on your team's specific AI prompt patterns in their first two weeks?</p>
        <div class="answer-row">
          <button class="ans-btn" data-answer="yes" data-q="5">Yes</button>
          <button class="ans-btn" data-answer="no" data-q="5">No</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="question" data-q="6">
        <span class="qnum">Question 6 of 8</span>
        <p class="qtext">Have you consolidated to fewer than four primary AI/LLM platforms across the company?</p>
        <div class="answer-row">
          <button class="ans-btn" data-answer="yes" data-q="6">Yes</button>
          <button class="ans-btn" data-answer="no" data-q="6">No</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="question" data-q="7">
        <span class="qnum">Question 7 of 8</span>
        <p class="qtext">Do you measure AI productivity gains (hours saved, throughput per worker) as a real metric, not a vague line item?</p>
        <div class="answer-row">
          <button class="ans-btn" data-answer="yes" data-q="7">Yes</button>
          <button class="ans-btn" data-answer="no" data-q="7">No</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="question" data-q="8">
        <span class="qnum">Question 8 of 8</span>
        <p class="qtext">Have you deleted at least one full workflow (not just accelerated one) because AI made it unnecessary?</p>
        <div class="answer-row">
          <button class="ans-btn" data-answer="yes" data-q="8">Yes</button>
          <button class="ans-btn" data-answer="no" data-q="8">No</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="progress">
        <span class="progress-text" id="progress-text">0 of 8 answered</span>
        <div class="progress-bar"><div class="progress-fill" id="progress-fill" style="width:0%"></div></div>
        <button class="btn-g" id="reset-btn" style="padding:0.5rem 1rem;font-size:0.78rem;">Reset</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="result-card" id="result-card">
      <span class="tier-tag" id="tier-tag"></span>
      <h2 class="tier-head" id="tier-head">Your AI maturity tier</h2>
      <p class="tier-score" id="tier-score"></p>
      <p class="tier-verdict" id="tier-verdict"></p>
      <span class="rec-head">Your three next steps</span>
      <ul class="rec-list" id="rec-list"></ul>
      <div class="rec-actions">
        <a href="/quiz" class="btn-p">Take the deeper Gap Assessment &rarr;</a>
        <button class="btn-g" id="share-btn">Share these results</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">About the methodology</span>
    <h2 class="h2">Where these 8 questions come from</h2>
    <p class="body">The four tier names (Exploring, Piloting, Operationalizing, Compounding) come from the framework we used in the <a href="/state-of-ai-native-gtm-2026" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;">2026 State of AI-Native GTM</a> report. The eight questions are the leading indicators that most consistently separated tier from tier in the underlying data.</p>
    <p class="body">For the deeper mid-market view, including median scores by company size, see the <a href="/mid-market-ai-maturity-benchmark-2026" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;">Mid-Market AI Maturity Benchmark 2026</a>. For the full operating model the tiers describe, see <a href="/the-ai-native-gtm-framework" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;">the AI-native GTM framework</a>.</p>
    <p class="body">Each "yes" is worth 1 point. 0 to 2 points is Tier 1 (Exploring). 3 to 4 is Tier 2 (Piloting). 5 to 6 is Tier 3 (Operationalizing). 7 to 8 is Tier 4 (Compounding). The tier maps directly to a specific set of next moves, not a generic readiness score.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">FAQ</span>
    <h2 class="h2">Common questions</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3 class="faq-q">What is "AI maturity"?</h3>
      <p class="faq-a">AI maturity is how deeply AI is woven into how a team actually works. Not how many tools you own, not how many demos you've watched. The signal is behavior change: whether real workflows have been rebuilt, whether new hires inherit AI patterns, and whether you've deleted work because AI made it unnecessary.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3 class="faq-q">Why these 8 questions?</h3>
      <p class="faq-a">Each question maps to a leading indicator we see correlate with real AI-native operating behavior in the 2026 State of AI-Native GTM dataset. CEO usage, a named AI lead with protected time, workflows in production, documentation, training, tool consolidation, productivity measurement, and workflow deletion. Teams that score high on these eight tend to compound. Teams that score low tend to plateau.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3 class="faq-q">How accurate is this for my team?</h3>
      <p class="faq-a">It's a directional self-diagnostic, not a paid audit. Eight questions cannot capture every nuance. But the tier you land in is almost always the tier a deeper assessment would also place you in. If you score on a boundary (3 vs 4 points, or 6 vs 7), you're transitioning, and the lower tier's next steps still apply.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3 class="faq-q">What if I get a tier I don't like?</h3>
      <p class="faq-a">Tier 1 and Tier 2 are where most mid-market teams sit in 2026. That's not a verdict, it's a starting line. The recommendations are specific actions, in order, that move teams up one tier within a quarter. Pick the first one and start. Don't try to jump two tiers at once.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3 class="faq-q">How is this different from the Treetop Gap Assessment?</h3>
      <p class="faq-a">This calculator gives you a tier in 60 seconds. The Treetop Gap Assessment is a deeper 15 minute diagnostic that maps your specific workflows, scores each function (sales, marketing, customer success, ops), and produces a 90 day rollout plan. Use this calculator first. If the tier surprises you, take the Gap Assessment to understand why.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">Related</span>
    <h2 class="h2">Related guides</h2>
    <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;color:#C0D8C0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.85;">
      <li style="padding:0.5rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;"><a href="/state-of-ai-native-gtm-2026" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;">2026 State of AI-Native GTM (flagship report) &rarr;</a></li>
      <li style="padding:0.5rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;"><a href="/mid-market-ai-maturity-benchmark-2026" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;">Mid-Market AI Maturity Benchmark 2026 &rarr;</a></li>
      <li style="padding:0.5rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;"><a href="/the-ai-native-gtm-framework" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;">The AI-native GTM framework &rarr;</a></li>
      <li style="padding:0.5rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;"><a href="/best-ai-tools-for-consultants-2026" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;">Best AI tools for consultants (2026) &rarr;</a></li>
      <li style="padding:0.5rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;"><a href="/services/ai-audit" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;">Treetop AI Audit service &rarr;</a></li>
